manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Choose Magcubic Projector, and you will get higher quality Home Theater Projector at an affordable cost! Magcubic projector offers stunning image: 720p, supports 4K video playback, stunning brightness (200 ANSI 8000 lumens brightness), excellent 10000:1 contrast ratio and 16:9/4:3 aspect ratio.This supported 4K projector is equipped with 2.4G & 5G dual Wi-Fi 6 connections. Dual wifi connection can ensure a stable signal and fast transmission speed.With Android 11.0 has a built-in operating system, allowing it to function as a stand-alone device.It comes with BT 5.0 function, which supports stable connection to various BT speakers, you can enjoy music with your own BT specker.This portable projector offers autofocus function. The autofocus system is highly accurate and can quickly focus on a subject without the need to manually adjust focus.Projectors also provide automatic horizontal keystone correction and manual trapezoidal correction. By combining two functions, you will get better viewing experience, better image quality.Built-in screen mirroring function, supports Miracast, Airplay, DLNA. Mirror your screen from anywhere!This projector is powered by ARM Mali-G31 MP2 GPU is best in image processing. Provides users with a great experience of ultra-fast processing speed and professional image processing capability.With surprisingly powerful audio so you don't need to buy external sound system for this projector. Taking you on an unforgettable musical journey.The projector offers a projection size of 40"-200" with a projection distance between 4.9ft-18.4ft, you can get the best viewing size by manual adjustment.Multi-device connection. Built-in HD, AV, USB, 3.5mm headphone port, plus included HD cable, TV Stick/Box connection, game consoles, PCs, smartphones, tablets, laptops and USB pen drives.

Mirror your screen from anywhere! Wireless projection is easy to operate and eliminates space and cable limitations, allowing you to enjoy the large screen in minutes. Miracast Make sure Android devices (phone, pad, etc) are on the same local wireless LAN with these devices Device operations: Home → My Applications → Miracast → Miracast Open → Turn on phone mirroring → Connection Airplay Make sure Android devices (phone, pad, etc) are on the same local wireless LAN with these devices Home → My Applications → Air Pin → Outdoor Pin → Turn on phone mirroring → Connection Please note that due to copyright restrictions, certain platforms such as Netflix, Amazon Prime and Disney+ do not allow mirrored display. But don't worry! You can even use a TV stick with the projector to enjoy these videos.

Android 11.0 & 4000+ Apps This smart projector with pre-installed Android 11.0 smart system and Google Play Store, which allows you to download over 4000 apps, access online, browse the Internet and run apps seamlessly. No need to buy expensive TV sticks, just log into your account and watch all your favorite series with this projector. You can watch movies, football games, variety programs, enjoy the joy of the big screen in the cinema instantly.

Adopted high performance GPU This WiFi projector uses ARM Mali-G31 MP2-GPU and is designed to provide high quality graphics for mobile devices such as smartphones and tablets. Overall, the ARM Mali-G31 MP2 provides an excellent balance between performance, energy efficiency and advanced functionality, making it an ideal choice for multiple mobile devices. One of the advantages of this GPU is its low power consumption, making it very suitable for use on battery-powered devices. It also supports graphics APIs including OpenGL ES 3.2, Vulkan 1.0 and OpenCL 2.0. Another advantage of the ARM Mali-G31 MP2 is its ability to support high resolution displays with resolutions up to 1080p. It can support 4K decoding, intelligent clarity, anti aliasing, image enhancement and image denoising. This makes it the best choice for devices that require high definition graphics such as gaming devices and virtual reality headsets. The GPU also has a number of optimization functions, including advanced texture compression, which helps reduce memory requirements and improve system performance. It also supports hardware security features to help protect user data from potential security threats.

BT 5.0 & Built-in HiFi Speaker This home theater has HiFi Speaker which can provide high quality sound with better clarity, precision and fidelity, improving the overall listening experience. So you don't need to buy audio devices, using our projector you can get picture and sound as good as your local cinema. And this smart projector also integrated BT 5.0, which can offer faster speed, longer range and improved connectivity compared to previous versions, making it easier to connect and use devices without interruption. You can connect ideal headphones, speakers or other audio equipment.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Solid Depending on Your Needs
reviews.reviewText: I have tried about six projectors of varying prices and designs, and this is the one that I decided to keep. Overall I like the projector for my needs: I use it in a smaller bedroom to watch TV and I take it places to project on walls.Pros:Low costSmall and lightSelf-contained standAdjustable angle stand (but cannot adjust all the way to vertical if HDMI connected)Easy to setupAuto and manual keystone correctionElectronic Zoom in and out (many projectors do not have this feature)Fan noise sounds more like a noise machine than a high-pitched or distracting fan.Cons:Not super bright; works best in a darker roomLower picture quality than others (but still decent when dark and set up properly)Slight light around the edges of picture when you zoom in (but not that noticeable)Sound is weak, but okay for most showsAngle adjustment is not free, it locks into certain angles, which can make it more difficult to position the image precisely where you want itAll control goes through remote, so if that breaks, I guess I'm out of luck (I plan to try to buy a backup)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars My Experience with the Mini Projector
reviews.reviewText: This product has been nothing short of a complete disaster, and I can't help but share my intense dissatisfaction with you.Here are some of the infuriating issues I've encountered:Upon turning it on, the projector stubbornly displays only the "Miracast" setup page, effectively locking me out of accessing any other features or the home screen. It's as if the projector has become a one-trick pony.Bluetooth pairing with my phone appears to work, but it's utterly pointless since it fails to deliver any functionality. Moreover, attempting to use it with HDMI out on my PC is an exercise in frustration. The placement of the HDMI port on the back is a design flaw that hinders vertical rotation with an HDMI connector, making it incredibly inconvenient.Despite numerous attempts to adjust the settings, the image quality remains consistently and infuriatingly blurry, undermining the very purpose of a projector.To add insult to injury, my initial purchase was a colossal waste of money and time. The product arrived broken, a testament to the utter lack of quality control. It's maddening that this fraudulent company would knowingly send out defective items. The projector doesn't connect to any smart devices or Wi-Fi as advertised, and the screen quality is nothing short of abysmal.
